messages.text: The company that built codewars, Qualified. Also has another tool called <http://Qualified.io|Qualified.io> that is used for developer technical interviews. So keep at it!
And then some. Thank you, Oli!

Definitely the process of learning “just in time” is part of becoming a better developer.

“I don’t know how to do this”
“How would I do this?”
“What is this new thing”
“Let me try this new thing”
“I didn’t even know I could do that”
“I now know how to use this new thing”

That said to answer your initial question. 

I wouldn’t be looking up “solutions”. I do think think it is valid to start by doing some pseudocode to try to write in english what you think the the solution should be and then along the way read through the mozilla developer network javascript documentation to try to find tools to help you toward your solution.
Thank you. This is a great resource.
I tend to avoid any that have the tag “Bugs” or something similar.
This will provide you a list of all the katas from easiest to hardest for javascript that have been approved.
